                    <div class="rich-text">
    <div id="parent-fieldname-text">
      <p>
        <span><strong><i><a href="http://www.dph.ox.ac.uk/bhfhprg/research-themes/physicalactivity/applications">COURSE APPLICATIONS NOW OPEN.</a></i></strong></span>
      </p>
      <p>
        <span>We are delighted to announce a brand new training course in evaluation for physical activity. This will be a 2.5 day event in the lead up to the ISBNPA 2015 conference in Edinburgh, UK. The course is aimed at early career researchers, practitioners and policy makers seeking to develop their evaluation skills and knowledge.</span>
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="http://www.dph.ox.ac.uk/bhfhprg/research-themes/physicalactivity/Web%20flyer%20v5.pdf">Download the Course Flyer here (pdf)</a>
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Objectives and content</strong>
      </p>
      <p>
        This course has been designed to build evaluation capacity in physical activity research and practice. <a title="" href="http://bhfcpnp.medsci.ox.ac.uk/upcoming-events/training-course-pragmatic-evaluation-in-physical-activity-public-health/pepa-course-description.pdf" target="_self">See the full course description and content here.</a>
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Facult<span>y</span></strong>
      </p>
      <p>
        <span>This course will feature teaching from world leading experts including Prof Adrian Bauman, Prof Nanette Mutrie, Dr David Ogilvie and Prof Charlie Foster.</span>
      </p>
      <p>
        <span><strong>Application process</strong></span>
      </p>
      <p>
        <span>Applications for the 2015 course are now open. <a title="" href="http://bhfcpnp.medsci.ox.ac.uk/upcoming-events/training-course-pragmatic-evaluation-in-physical-activity-public-health/pepa_application-form-2015.docx" target="_self">The application form is available here.</a> If you have any questions, please email us at</span> <span><span><a href="mailto:pragmatic.evaluation@gmail.com">pragmatic.evaluation@gmail.com</a></span></span>
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Location</strong>
      </p>
      <p>
        This course will be hosted by the <span><a href="http://www.ed.ac.uk/schools-departments/education/rke/centres-groups/pahrc" target="_blank" title="">Physical Activity for Health Research Centre</a></span> at the historic <span><a href="http://www.ed.ac.uk/home" target="_blank">University of Edinburgh</a></span>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <img class="image-inline" src="http://www.dph.ox.ac.uk/resolveuid/2fe0e3c5e95b7b6ccc658d3a1b4fdb1a/@@images/image/mini" alt="" /></p>
      <p>
        <span><strong>Organising Committee</strong></span>
      </p>
      <p>
        This course is a collaboration between researchers from the University of Sydney, the University of Edinburgh and the University of Oxford.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Sponsor</strong>
      </p>
      <p>
        We are grateful for the support of <span><a href="http://www.paltechnologies.com/" target="_blank">PAL Technologies</a></span> - our official course sponsor
      </p>
      <p>
        <img class="image-inline" src="http://www.dph.ox.ac.uk/resolveuid/a9afeb2d8e3e0c9f487f76390dc3aa17/@@images/image/preview" alt="" /></p>
      <p>
        <strong>Official partners</strong>
      </p>
      <p>
        This course has been officially recognised by:
      </p>
      <ul><li>The International Society for Physical Activity and Health (ISPAH)
        </li>
        <li>The ISPAH Early Career Network
        </li>
        <li>The WHO Collaborating Centre for Physical Activity, Nutrition and Obesity
        </li>
        <li>The International Society for Behavioural Nutrition and Physical Activity (ISBNPA)
        </li>
      </ul><p>
        <img class="image-inline" src="http://www.dph.ox.ac.uk/resolveuid/33238e16c098d4095cc3e188316a0ced/@@images/image/preview" alt="" /></p>
      <p>
        <img class="image-inline" src="http://www.dph.ox.ac.uk/resolveuid/7e4f1d7d37c09aed710500c592b77620" alt="" /></p>
      <p>
        <img class="image-inline" src="http://www.dph.ox.ac.uk/resolveuid/8c914f42cf6791dae5711f8fc292c519/@@images/image/mini" alt="" /></p>
    </div>
